  "text": "The purpose then seen from previous to incarnation of what we call the incarnate physical state seems to be holy or almost holy that of experiencing at this at that point the programmed catalyst and then evolving as a function of that catalyst. Is that correct? I am we shall restate for clarity the purpose of incarnative existence is evolution of mind, body and spirit. In order to do this, it is not strictly necessary to have catalyst, however, without catalyst, the desire to evolve and the faith in the process do not normally manifest, and thus evolution occurs not. Thus it is desirable that a mind, body, spirit complex be aware of and hearken to the voice of its experiential catalyst, gleaning from it that which it incarnated to glean.",
